text: Sullivan County is a county in the U.S. state of New Hampshire. As of the 2020 census, the population was 43,063, making it the second-least populous county in New Hampshire. The county seat is Newport. Sullivan County was founded in 1827 named for John Sullivan (1740â€“1795), the Revolutionary War hero and a former governor.
